			<description><![CDATA[<p>
Aarki is looking for the best and the brightest to join our team of rock stars. You&rsquo;re looking for the perfect place to put that put your experience to use and make it count. This is a great opportunity to work with a company that is changing the face of mobile advertising technology. If you think you&rsquo;ve got what it takes, read on.</p>
<p>
<strong>Responsibilities</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Manage pre-launch preparation activities such as client-on boarding and kick off calls and all post-sales ad campaign execution activities for assigned advertising accounts, including custom unit approvals, project management, campaign operations</li>
<li>
Manage the set-up process for new ad campaigns, including integration, uploading, scheduling, launching, tracking, and reporting of ad campaigns</li>
<li>
Obtain creative materials from internal and external parties (advertisers/agencies), ensure all advertising assets are accurately captured</li>
<li>
Manage the ad test &amp; QA process, ensuring ads display properly on mobile devices, the creative meets specs, and click-through works properly</li>
<li>
Track the progress of advertising campaigns from conception to delivery by monitoring deadlines, billing, and advertisements scheduling and placement</li>
<li>
Work with clients to monitor, revise, and optimize ad campaigns to ensure full delivery and achieve optimal creative performance</li>
<li>
Troubleshoot and communicate with internal Sales team and external parties (advertisers/agencies) on creative and operational campaign performance issues as well as inaccuracies or problems, providing suggestions to optimize conversion rates and delivery</li>
<li>
Work closely with internal Ad Sales and Publishing Teams and external ad networks/agencies to ensure that we are meeting our various advertiser &amp; publisher goals and targets</li>
<li>
Support the sales team, be the point of contact for all post sale communication between client/agency relating to ad campaigns (including but not limited to trafficking questions/concerns/requests, acquiring assets, confirming optimizations, revised IO&rsquo;s, billing questions, delivery questions, reporting questions, concerns regarding response of other team members)</li>
<li>
Report to advertising sales agents on the status and placement of campaigns to guarantee correct billing</li>
<li>
Provide prompt and accurate advertising metrics to clients</li>
<li>
Provide prompt and professional responses to client inquiries via phone &amp; e-mail</li>
<li>
Prepare mid and post campaign reporting for assigned accounts</li>
<li>
Provide weekly and quarterly sales projection reporting to senior management</li>
<li>
Generate and analyze internal and 3rd party reports for billing and contract reconciliation</li>
<li>
Work with product managers and engineers to identify process inefficiencies; to recommend, design, develop, test, implement, and document new tools, systems, processes, and features that will improve advertising operations workflow and increase yield</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Requirements</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
One year experience in digital/mobile ad operations in either a trafficking or sales support role</li>
<li>
Familiarity with ad serving technologies/platforms and 3rd parties servers</li>
<li>
Knowledge of ad serving concepts (CPM/CPA/RTB/ROI), video, mobile, social a plus</li>
<li>
Ability to work as part of a team as well as independently to recognize, troubleshoot, and solve problems. Critical thinking and common sense are essential to success in this role</li>
<li>
Strong analytical and metrics oriented mindset that can not only process quantitative results but also provide actionable suggestions based on these results</li>
<li>
Experience working with a sales force with tight deadlines and turn arounds</li>
<li>
Excellent time-management, organizational, and client/customer service skills</li>
<li>
Excellent written and verbal communication skills for internal and client facing emails and reports</li>
<li>
Extremely detail-oriented, exceptionally organized</li>
<li>
Ability to multi-task, prioritize, and manage multiple campaigns at once</li>
<li>
Comfortable in a technical environment</li>
<li>
Must be proficient in Microsoft Office (specifically Word, Excel, and PowerPoint).</li>
<li>
Self-starter who requires little supervision or direction and ask for guidance when needed</li>
<li>
Thrives in a fast-paced, deadline-oriented startup environment</li>
<li>
A passion for all things mobile</li>
<li>
Exhibit enthusiasm, passion, creativity and commitment</li>
<li>
Have a positive attitude and strong work ethic</li>
<li>
College degree with emphasis in Engineering, Computer Science, Statistics, Advertising or analytical field</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Perks</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Work with and learn from best-in-class teams; our employees rock!</li>
<li>
You&rsquo;ll be part of a mid-stage startup with huge upside</li>
<li>
Fast paced and challenging projects</li>
<li>
Diverse and forward-thinking leadership</li>
<li>
Stocked kitchen with tons of free snacks and coffee</li>
<li>
Competitive salary, benefits, and lots of stock options</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Company Description</strong></p>
<p>
Aarki is a mobile monetization and advertising platform. Aarki&#39;s rich media interstitial ads deliver engaged users and increased monetization. Video ads and mobile optimized brand offers result in the best user experience. The management of app distribution campaigns on Aarki&#39;s self serve platform is simple and efficient.</p>
