			<description><![CDATA[<p>
As the Performance Advertising Manager at Aarki you will be responsible for identifying, procuring, and managing a wide variety of lead generation (Cost Per Action/Lead) ad campaigns globally. Campaigns are prospected, evaluated, and incorporated into the Aarki platform through a broad range of sources and partnerships. You are responsible for developing these partnerships for our performance advertising business, implementing quantitative metrics, increasing conversion rates, and optimizing revenue. You will ensure that Aarki has the most comprehensive performance ad campaign inventory and that such campaigns are revenue optimized.</p>
<p>
Responsibilities:</p>
<ul>
<li>
Lead a team of associates &amp; ad traffickers to manage the ad campaign life cycle: including sales, trafficking, tracking, reporting, and optimization</li>
<li>
Ensure that Aarki has the most accurate, consistent, high quality, and comprehensive collection of performance ad campaigns</li>
<li>
Work with existing sources of advertisers in entering, updating, and maintaining campaigns (descriptions, requirements, pricing, etc.), adding new campaigns and removing obsolete offers</li>
<li>
Actively develop and measure quantitative metrics, conversion rates, and revenue optimization</li>
<li>
Serve as the primary contact to partners (demand sources, advertisers, agencies) regarding all matters relating to performance campaigns</li>
<li>
Head-up research of relevant sources of performance campaigns globally, including new and emerging categories</li>
<li>
Collaborate with product management and provide guidance on ad trafficking features</li>
<li>
Own regular readouts on performance across Aarki&rsquo;s ad campaign inventory</li>
<li>
Risk management of arbitrage related to differential pricing</li>
<li>
Strategic planning, revenue forecasting, and market development analysis for new performance advertising categories</li>
<li>
Interface with the customer service team to resolve customer inquiries related to advertisements</li>
<li>
Monthly invoicing and management of accounts receivables</li>
</ul>
<p>
Experience &amp; Requirements:</p>
<ul>
<li>
3+ years of business development or account management experience in the performance advertising industry</li>
<li>
Experience in web based affiliate marketing, lead generation, and e-commerce</li>
<li>
A passion for all things mobile</li>
<li>
Good strategic thinking, sound business judgment, strong analytic aptitude, collaborative working style, coupled with a desire to deliver outstanding business impact</li>
<li>
Familiarity with ad serving technologies/platforms and 3rd parties servers</li>
<li>
Knowledge of ad pricing concepts (CPM/CPC/CPA)</li>
<li>
Excellent written and verbal communication skills for internal and client facing emails, calls, and reports</li>
<li>
Excellent quantitative, multi-tasking, prioritization, and organizational skills</li>
<li>
Extremely detail-oriented, exceptionally organized</li>
<li>
Exhibit enthusiasm, integrity, passion, creativity and commitment</li>
<li>
Have a positive attitude and strong work ethic</li>
<li>
Thrives in a fast-paced, deadline-oriented startup environment</li>
<li>
Self-starter who requires little supervision or direction and ask for guidance when needed</li>
</ul>
<p>
Perks:</p>
<ul>
<li>
Work with and learn from best-in-class teams; our employees rock!</li>
<li>
You&rsquo;ll be part of a mid-stage startup with huge upside</li>
<li>
Fast paced and challenging projects</li>
<li>
Diverse and forward-thinking leadership</li>
<li>
Stocked kitchen with tons of free snacks and coffee</li>
<li>
Competitive salary, benefits, and lots of stock options</li>
</ul>
